00:22:13.250 --> 00:22:16.260
So as you can see, our
game, as I said before,

00:22:16.260 --> 00:22:20.560
you control some toys
on a day at the beach.

00:22:27.360 --> 00:22:30.550
And so by dragging and dropping
them between the castles,

00:22:30.550 --> 00:22:33.280
you'll see that their
statuses change and say

00:22:33.280 --> 00:22:35.360
that they want to move
on their next turn,

00:22:35.360 --> 00:22:37.440
or that they want
to be collecting--

00:22:37.440 --> 00:22:41.240
or that they're going to be
collecting candy, or anything

00:22:41.240 --> 00:22:42.790
like that.

00:22:42.790 --> 00:22:44.990
And the game is turned based.

00:22:44.990 --> 00:22:48.160
So all the actions will
resolve on the next turn.

00:23:15.440 --> 00:23:19.904
ANDREW: Am I rating this race?

00:23:19.904 --> 00:23:20.629
MATT: Yeah.

00:23:20.629 --> 00:23:23.128
NORMAN: You can also access the
help through the lower right

00:23:23.128 --> 00:23:23.872
corner as well.

00:23:40.736 --> 00:23:43.690
MATT: And so when you
go to the next turn,

00:23:43.690 --> 00:23:48.940
you'll see all the toys move
as specified by the status

00:23:48.940 --> 00:23:50.782
bubble above their heads.

00:23:50.782 --> 00:23:56.494
ANDREW: So I go to the next
turn, or do I get a next turn?

00:23:56.494 --> 00:23:58.390
MATT: But unfortunately,
you'll find

00:23:58.390 --> 00:24:02.366
that when toys have been
evacuated, they're unhappy

00:24:02.366 --> 00:24:04.615
and need candy to survive,
so they'll all take damage.

00:24:07.822 --> 00:24:10.774
ANDREW: They don't
want you to evacuate.

00:24:10.774 --> 00:24:13.234
MATT: You can try returning
them to their homes.

00:24:29.962 --> 00:24:32.360
NORMAN: And so you'll
see that on this turn

00:24:32.360 --> 00:24:35.210
instead, now they have
their statuses set

00:24:35.210 --> 00:24:37.715
to gathering candy, except for
the dump truck, who is still

00:24:37.715 --> 00:24:38.215
evacuated.

00:24:46.394 --> 00:24:49.328
ANDREW: Got you, OK.

00:24:49.328 --> 00:24:50.795
But he needs to be evacuated.

00:24:58.130 --> 00:25:01.450
NORMAN: Exactly.

00:25:01.450 --> 00:25:03.927
And so the idea is that as
a player plays through it,

00:25:03.927 --> 00:25:06.260
they get better at understanding
how to use the forecast

00:25:06.260 --> 00:25:09.447
to make decisions
about the future,

00:25:09.447 --> 00:25:12.030
both in terms of how much candy
that they need to have stocked

00:25:12.030 --> 00:25:14.880
up in order to weather
out the rising tides

00:25:14.880 --> 00:25:17.100
and also in terms
of when they're

00:25:17.100 --> 00:25:19.610
going to need to move
their workers out

00:25:19.610 --> 00:25:22.244
of-- their toys out of the
areas that are in danger.

00:25:22.244 --> 00:25:24.077
ANDREW: They're going
to be really impacted.

00:25:58.636 --> 00:26:00.340
MATT: I think you
have those two guys.

00:26:00.340 --> 00:26:02.276
ANDREW: Oh, they're in there?

